cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.EDU 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on developing predictive models using machine learning techniques to predict whether a student's first job out of college will be in a STEM field or not. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses data from a longitudinal study and applies computational techniques to analyze the data and develop predictive models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep knowledge tracing models to estimate the expected knowledge state of students with respect to different mathematical skills. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to extract features from the student profile in the dataset. 
- cs.EDU (Education): The paper uses data from the ASSISTments blended learning platform and aims to predict a new outcome of students which had never been studied before by the educational data mining research community.
